<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-21T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/993: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Counselor of Embassy in China</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>),
                                    <hi rend="italic">at Chungking</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-21T16:00:00-05:00">February 21, 1940—4
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>25. Your 81, February 19, 9 a.m., extra-Settlement roads. It is
                                suggested that, as in the case mentioned in your 300, May 1, 3 p.m.,
                                    1939<note n="70" xml:id="d786fn70"><ref target="frus1939v04#pg_31"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>,
                                        p. 31</ref>.</note> (Chinese activities in International
                                Settlement), the Embassy make acknowledgement to the Foreign Office
                                to the effect that the matter has been referred to the
                                Department.</p>
                            <p>Sent to Chungking. Repeated to Peiping and Shanghai.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>